<li id="cite_note-52"><b><a href="#cite_ref-52" title="">^</a></b> <i><a href="http://www.bopsecrets.org/SI/12.era2.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.bopsecrets.org/SI/12.era2.htm" rel="nofollow">The Beginning of an Era</a></i> Situationist International #12, 1969</li>
<li id="cite_note-ClarkEtAlSpring97-53">^ <a href="#cite_ref-ClarkEtAlSpring97_53-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-ClarkEtAlSpring97_53-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-ClarkEtAlSpring97_53-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> Clark and Nicholson-Smith (Spring 1997), response to <a href="/wiki/Peter_Wollen" title="Peter Wollen">Peter Wollen</a>. Quote:
<blockquote>
<p>So far as Wollen is concerned, the anger was provoked by his essay on the history of the SI, and specifically his three-sentence treatment of the organization in its last decade. We think he should look again at these sentences (which conclude some thirty pages of discussion of the SI's place in modern art), and ask himself whether they are not lofty, contemptuous, and dismissive. That's how they read to us. They seem to epitomize—and, in view of their publication history, to enshrine—a certain effort to turn the SI safely into an <a href="/wiki/Art_movement" title="Art movement">art movement</a>, and thereby to minimize its role in the political and social movements of the sixties. Like Wollen, presumably, we think that those up-heavals are of much more than historical interest, and every day they are traduced and trivialized by the <a href="/wiki/Culture_industry" title="Culture industry">culture industry</a>. Much is at stake, therefore. We wanted to denounce a loose conspirancy of silence and misrepresentation which has been the response of a portion of the Left to the challenge that the SI poses to their model of political action.</p>
</blockquote>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-KnabbOnArtAndPolitics-54">^ <a href="#cite_ref-KnabbOnArtAndPolitics_54-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-KnabbOnArtAndPolitics_54-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Ken Knabb (2006) <i>SI Anthology</i>, Bibliography - Books about the SI - In English, p.498</li>
